<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[122,272,764,787]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis box="[122,272,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">O. melanopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
introduced also to North America) and can be frequently found on various 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[113,204,796,819]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
. Host plants of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Suffrian, 1847)" baseAuthorityName="Suffrian" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[380,721,796,819]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Lema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufocyanea">
<emphasis box="[380,535,796,819]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">O. rufocyanea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SUFFRIAN E." box="[552,713,796,819]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" pagination="98 - 102" refId="ref23088" refString="SUFFRIAN E. 1847: Zur Kritik einiger Kaferarten, nach Vergleich der Typen aus der Fabricius &quot; schen Sammlung. Entomologische Zeitung (Stettin) 8: 98 - 102." type="journal article" year="1847">Suffrian, 1847</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk &amp; Baselga, 2015" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Baselga" authorityYear="2015" box="[734,845,796,819]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauroi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[734,845,796,819]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">O. mauroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[854,942,796,819]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk &amp; Baselga, 2015" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Baselga" authorityYear="2015" box="[955,1049,796,819]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[955,1049,796,819]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">O. verae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="7" pageNumber="280" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are not known, but we presume also some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[628,715,828,851]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
species. 
<bibRefCitation author="ROZNER I. &amp; ROZNER G." box="[814,1089,828,851]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" pagination="111 - 131" refId="ref22727" refString="ROZNER I. &amp; ROZNER G. 2008: Data to the leaf-beetle fauna of Macedonia (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae). Natura Somogyiensis 12: 111 - 131." type="journal article" year="2008">ROZNER &amp; ROZNER (2008)</bibRefCitation>
published 
<taxonomicName box="[224,362,860,883]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Lamium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[224,311,860,883]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Lamium</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
as host plant of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Suffrian" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[538,691,860,883]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Lema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufocyanea">
<emphasis box="[538,691,860,883]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">O. rufocyanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[726,844,860,883]" name="Macedonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
but as other species of this group are associated with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[442,532,892,915]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
, the occurrence on 
<taxonomicName box="[742,882,892,915]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Lamium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[742,829,892,915]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Lamium</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
should be verified. Eastern Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kuwayama" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[324,427,924,947]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oryzae">
<emphasis box="[324,427,924,947]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">O. oryzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[629,765,924,947]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Oryza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativa">
<emphasis box="[629,765,924,947]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Oryza sativa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="281" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,220,1011]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1127,220,531]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="281" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,442,955,979]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Comments on identification.</emphasis>
All European species are habitually extremely similar. As shown in 
<tableCitation box="[221,289,988,1011]" captionStart="Tab" captionStartId="7.[115,149,1072,1091]" captionTargetBox="[124,1065,1120,1588]" captionText="Tab. 1. Measurments of Oulema species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2982663F5735B240FFEB6F52FE066121" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" tableUuid="2982663F5735B240FFEB6F52FE066121">Tab. 1</tableCitation>
, ratios of the main measurements widely overlap and cannot be used for species separation – with the exception of the elytral length / elytral width ratio which helps to separate three units: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Redtenbacher" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[396,552,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duftschmidi">
<emphasis box="[396,552,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">O. duftschmidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[603,751,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis box="[603,751,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">O. melanopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, intermediate 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk &amp; Baselga, 2015" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Baselga" authorityYear="2015" box="[903,994,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[903,994,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">O. verae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1000,1083,252,275]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and finally, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Suffrian" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[232,385,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Lema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufocyanea">
<emphasis box="[232,385,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">O. rufocyanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk &amp; Baselga, 2015" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Baselga" authorityYear="2015" box="[438,547,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oulema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauroi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[438,547,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">O. mauroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[555,638,284,307]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The absolute measurements seem to be more useful, particularly body length, elytral length, elyral width and length of antennae, but also here the measurements partially overlap. The only really reliable characters to distinguish the species are the shape of the flagellum in males and the shape of the spermatheca in females, particularly the length and shape of the soft distal part of ductus spermathecae and its junction to bursa copulatrix. Surprisingly, the shape of spermatheca itself is almost invariable in this group and, on the contrary, the shape and number of coils of the well sclerotized proximal part of ductus spermathecae seem to be too variable and can only partially be used for identification.
</paragraph>
